Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
moveSdpObject(25.10)                                      moveSdpObject(25.10)

Name
       moveSdpObject  - Moves specified SDP objects before or after the speci-
       fied reference object

Syntax
       moveSdpObject

       [-help]

       <moveObject >{<objName> <s>}

       {-before <refObject> | -after <refObject>}

       Moves specified SDP objects before or after the specified reference ob-
       ject. Use this command to:

              * Move a subgroup or member to a different position  within  the
                current SDP group

              * Move a subgroup or member to a different group to improve con-
                gestion and/or timing.

              * Move multiple instances, SDP groups, or a mix of instances and
                SDP groups to the specified location.

       In  the  traditional  SDP flow, this command can be used while defining
       SDP constraints or while analyzing SDP alignment.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each moveSdpObject parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man moveSdpObject.

       -after <refObject>
              Indicates  that  the specified SDP objects should be moved after
              the reference object:

              * For column with justifyBy SW/SE, after means the specified SDP
                objects are placed above the reference object.

              * For column with justifyBy NW/NE, after means the specified SDP
                objects are placed below the reference object.

              * For row with justifyBy SW/NW, after means that  the  specified
                SDP  objects are placed on the right side of the reference ob-
                ject.

              * For row with justifyBy SE/NE, after means that  the  specified
                SDP  objects  are placed on the left side of the reference ob-
                ject.

       -before <refObject>
              Indicates that the specified SDP objects should be moved  before
              the reference object:

              * For  column  with  justifyBy SW/SE, before means the specified
                SDP objects are placed below the reference object.

              * For column with justifyBy NW/NE, before  means  the  specified
                SDP objects are placed above the reference object.

              * For  row with justifyBy SW/NW, before means that the specified
                SDP objects are placed on the left side of the  reference  ob-
                ject.

              * For  row with justifyBy SE/NE, before means that the specified
                SDP objects are placed on the right side of the reference  ob-
                ject.

       <moveObject> {<objNames>}
              Specifies  the names of the SDP objects to be moved. The objects
              can be SDP groups, instances, or a mix of both.

              If multiple SDP objects are specified, the option works as  fol-
              lows:

              *

                If  both  the objects being moved and the reference object are
                instances, the instances being moved will  become  members  of
                the SDP group to which the reference instance belongs.

              * If  both  the objects being moved and the reference object are
                SDP groups, the SDP groups being moved will become members  of
                the SDP group to which the reference SDP group belongs.

              *

                If  the  objects  being moved are SDP groups and the reference
                object is an instance, the SDP groups being moved will  become
                members  of  the SDP group to which the reference instance be-
                longs.

              * If the objects being moved are instances and the reference ob-
                ject is an SDP group, the instances being  moved  will  become
                members  of the SDP group to which the reference SDP group be-
                longs.

              *

                If the objects being moved are a  mix  of  instances  and  SDP
                groups  and the reference object is an instance, the instances
                and SDP groups being moved will  become  members  of  the  SDP
                group  to  which the reference instance belongs and the result
                is based on the input sequence.

              *

                If the objects being moved are a  mix  of  instances  and  SDP
                groups and the reference object is an SDP group, the instances
                and  SDP  groups  being  moved  will become members of the SDP
                group to which the reference SDP group belongs and the  result
                is based on the input sequence.

Examples
              * The following command moves the SDP group sdpGrp1, which is an
                SDP  group of type row with justifyBy SE, to the right side of
                the group sdpGrp3:

                moveSdpObject sdpGrp1 -before sdpGrp3

              * The following command moves the SDP group SDP_col145, which is
                an SDP group of typecolumn with justifyBy NE, to the  position
                below SDP_col170.

                moveSdpObject SDP_col145 -after SDP_col170

              * Consider the SDP group structure given below:

                column group1 {

                   justifyBy SW

                    row selInstGrp_9 {

                       justifyBy SW

                       inst DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/ar1_reg_1

                       inst   DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/ar1_reg_13
                orient MX

                       inst DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/ar1_reg_12

                       inst DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/ar1_reg_3

                       inst   DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/ar0_reg_12
                orient R0

                       inst   DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/ar0_reg_13
                orient MX

                       inst
                DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/PORT_BUS_MACH_INST/data_out_reg_8

                       inst DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/ar1_reg_14

                    }

                   .....

                }

                *

                  The following command moves the specified  instances  before
                  selInstGrp_9:

                  moveSdpObject                 {DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXE-
                  CUTE_INST/acc_reg_30           DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXE-
                  CUTE_INST/acc_reg_32} -before selInstGrp_9

                  The resulting structure is as follows:

                  column group1 {

                      justifyBy SW

                      inst DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/acc_reg_30

                      inst DTME_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/acc_reg_32

                      row selInstGrp_9 {

                         justifyBy SW

                         inst DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/ar1_reg_1

                         inst DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/ar1_reg_13
                  orient MX

                         inst DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/ar1_reg_12

                         inst DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/ar1_reg_3

                         inst DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/ar0_reg_12
                  orient R0

                         inst DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/ar0_reg_13
                  orient MX

                         inst
                  DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/PORT_BUS_MACH_INST/data_out_reg_8

                         inst DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/ar1_reg_14

                      }

                     .....

                  }

                *

                  The  following  command  moves the specified instances after
                  selInstGrp_9:

                  moveSdpObject                 {DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXE-
                  CUTE_INST/acc_reg_30           DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXE-
                  CUTE_INST/acc_reg_32} -after selInstGrp_9

                  The resulting structure is as follows:

                  column group1 {

                     justifyBy SW

                     row selInstGrp_9 {

                        justifyBy SW

                        inst DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/ar1_reg_1

                        inst  DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/ar1_reg_13
                  orient MX

                        inst DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/ar1_reg_12

                        inst DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/ar1_reg_3

                        inst  DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/ar0_reg_12
                  orient R0

                        inst  DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/ar0_reg_13
                  orient MX

                        inst
                  DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/PORT_BUS_MACH_INST/data_out_reg_8

                        inst DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/ar1_reg_14

                     }

                     inst DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/acc_reg_30

                     inst DTME_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/acc_reg_32

                     .....

                  }

